        "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
        "body": "This is really cool! So the idea would be example repos with testing that matches code tutorials, recipes, etc?\r\nI like the concept a lot though I do wonder what kind of impact that will have on the size of the repo. We'd end up duplicating the code in both written form and project form. It's likely worth it, but I suspect we have duplication in written code steps as well, so perhaps an audit of that to make sure we aren't testing the same code paths would make sense?",
