        "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
        "body": "> the idea would be example repos with testing that matches code tutorials, recipes, etc?\r\n\r\nYep. I'm proposing writing simple tests for each one, but not necessarily running them with CI. That impact would be way larger. These are mostly for more robust source code examples that people can reference.\r\n\r\n> We'd end up duplicating the code in both written form and project form. It's likely worth it, but I suspect we have duplication in written code steps as well, so perhaps an audit of that to make sure we aren't testing the same code paths would make sense?\r\n\r\nI would definitely say it's worth it to have more examples, as users can grab those as starting points and play around with them without even having to follow the recipe. It lowers the barrier to entry that much more. What do you mean by \"an audit of [duplication in written code steps]\" in terms of testing code paths? I didn't quite follow. The tests I'm proposing will be based on the final output, not a branching scenario.",
