    {
        "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
        "body": "Certainly could have been clearer. I was thinking about the larger code coverage we'd be aiming for by having numerous example repos and matching tests. I suspect that in the process of aiming to cover snippets in both tutorials and recipes (and maybe more) we'd end up with similar if not identical projects. For example, baseline gatsby-image functionality. \r\nIt's not an immediate concern, but in order to cover the largest amount of code snippets represented in the docs we may want to perform some sort of audit at large to determine what documents to focus on. Rather than divvying up each doc and assuming the code involved is sufficiently discrete.\r\nI may still be struggling to explain this, but it's more of a meta consideration rather than something we need to solve as part of this PR.\r\n\r\nMy main question out of this PR is how/when are we triggering the testing suite so that we can consistently confirm expected behavior?",
